Tweet text: Have #data questions? We have data answers! Find the #datahelpdesk at #ESA2020's #CareerCentral, and watch our presentations (https://t.co/wuQmqS0G3G) to learn new data skills. Tweet any questions with #datahelpdesk and we'll help to answer them! https://t.co/n3ljppJDCD https://t.co/Lz4RUPU0no

#SharingSciFri: we're "going" to the @ESA_org #ESA2020 annual meeting! Come "see" us at the virtual booth with @DataONEorg & watch our talks to get your #datahelpdesk questions answered. All talks & associated links are collected here in this blog post! https://t.co/hHvYGynE3w https://t.co/jA0kd8GmgR
We're giving a few of the talks at #CareerCentral for this year's #ESA2020! https://t.co/1wxzOV2DSn

Starting in one hour - the @IARPCCollab Sub Team meeting focusing on Arctic data, where we'll be presenting on takeaways from a workshop we recently held on supporting #socialscience data. Join us! https://t.co/Slt5YbrekV https://t.co/1z9Il1DW3F
We'll be there! Blog post forthcoming about what talks we're giving and where to "find" us. https://t.co/yFesVGcPLG

In case you missed it, celebrate #WisdomWednesday by taking time to read the #AOS2020 conference statement, which summarizes the main conclusions and call to action from the Arctic Observing Summit (@arcticchange1) that convened online in April. https://t.co/AiPs0PiLQV https://t.co/ZabpazxxM3
@polargriffin We often combine illustrations from https://t.co/HGt36c5ctk if you're looking for some clip art graphics.

For today’s #TravelTuesday, we’re going meta - highlighting research about #travel and #tourism in the Arctic in this special edition of the Journal of Tourism Futures. Pre-COVID, of course. https://t.co/91ASKfr3BG https://t.co/fSi8MPqe45

On Thursday this week, join Erin McLean from the @arcticdatactr at the virtual @IARPCCollab Data Sub-Team Meeting focused on supporting #SocialScience data in the #Arctic. https://t.co/Slt5YbrekV https://t.co/J6WUQF9nDK

We participated in and won a FUNding Friday award from @ESIPfed! Can't wait to help make it easy for researchers to answer the question of where to put their data. @aebudden's design work is great! https://t.co/tzMTa0zel6

As #permafrost thaws, what happens to the #bacteria that live there? Ricketts et al investigate in a #NewPaper about bacterial abundance in warming soils. Read the paper (https://t.co/uOx3fQ7BMc) & for more, here's another bacteria dataset from Ricketts (https://t.co/Ss04JwC9Q9). https://t.co/YYJwAIbNA0
Join us next week! https://t.co/A1xoTs5a6A

This #WildWednesday brings you good news about little auks - they show a lot of flexibility in their foraging habits in warm and cold years, and chick survival was similar regardless of average #Arctic sea surface temp. Read the #openaccess paper here: https://t.co/M6RVB0HK8J https://t.co/0iROWmXXP6
Such a useful resource for #scicomm in a #virtual world! https://t.co/ViEeeyonMv

Our Director of Learning and Outreach, @aebudden, is giving a talk today with colleagues at the @ESIPfed Summer Meeting on Supporting the Earth Science Community in Data Discovery. Learn more here - hope to see you there! https://t.co/LFPrSCyDFb #esipfed https://t.co/RngdU3jTKa
Thanks for joining us! @timpasch @noorjohnson @ArchaeoHacker @nniiicc @mercecrosas @kristalj1982 @andrewstuhl @clcarothers @chutneyboy & everyone else!

New blog post alert - what was discussed at the @arcticdatactr's workshop on supporting #Arctic #SocialScience data? Find out here in this month's blog. https://t.co/YG4PA9tceU https://t.co/cwVi4xMjwc

#OverlyHonestMethods from a paper on fecal microbiota in #Arctic birds for your #FieldworkFriday: "The bird droppings were collected...avoiding...fecal material that was touching the ground to avoid soil contamination using sterile plastic spoons." https://t.co/hm3UcPhm38 https://t.co/DReVuEvXqa

Multimedia journal issue? About #polar research? To celebrate scientific #progress, increase topic awareness, and identify opportunities for #collaboration? Can't wait. Researchers - submit your work! Deadline 8/24. https://t.co/7TwS02AYAL https://t.co/kHeYsEbL22

The PI of the Arctic Data Center, @metamattj, is giving a talk with colleagues at the @ESIPfed Summer Meeting today on Advancing https://t.co/H3y1ZpnkMY Guidelines for Dataset Interoperability & Discovery. Learn more here & hope to see you there! https://t.co/XM2uLid7Qo #esipfed https://t.co/PFhDUfrY9M

@PolarImpact We're working on a set of educational modules using data from the Arctic Data Center - and we're hoping to feature datasets from underrepresented groups. We'll let you know when they're ready!
We're a member node of DataONE - excited to see this new look! https://t.co/Rr0nx6Gjyg

Our own @metamattj and @aebudden are presenting today and tomorrow with colleagues at the @ESIPfed Summer Meeting's session on Structured Data on the Web: Putting Best Practice to Work. More info here and hope to see you there! https://t.co/5Plda6Xve1 #esipfed https://t.co/PnCvQPlA9E

The @ArcticSynthesis is looking for #manuscript submissions! Does your work highlight important needs, explore emerging opportunities, address challenges, or present new initiatives that can contribute to #Arctic observing? Submit by Sept 1! #SharingSciFri https://t.co/BzWRGmUbZW https://t.co/aYOjGnxVSe

The @IARPCCollab Diversity & Inclusion Team is seeking self-nominations from members of the Arctic research community (in particular, Black, Indigenous, and People of Color) to become co-leads of the team - share to your colleagues! https://t.co/cpJUJMoWDd

This #WildWednesday, we’re highlighting a paper about #PolarBear denning that used many sources of #data to produce a full distribution of where these bears den and where we have gaps in our knowledge. Read more from @KFlorko et al: https://t.co/lIPb2pge4J https://t.co/qmLBeYbDqP

#NewPaper on how #Arctic #science influences Arctic #politics - the #GoodNewsTues takeaway is that nations agree that #international scientific #cooperation stimulates cooperation also in other areas. More like @MOSAiCArctic may bring nations together. https://t.co/rj47zgujzr https://t.co/KX6H564puU
Easing into Monday with this #glacier tour! https://t.co/mffjS0luy6

#SharingSciFri: @IARPCCollab is looking for input on the structure, goals, and objectives for the 2022-2026 Arctic Research Plan. Share your ideas on the critical issues facing the #Arctic and what #research needs to be done to address them. Find out more: https://t.co/Aax18TZWog https://t.co/GzUiQVzLpW

With #DataScience one of the fastest-growing fields in the 21st century, it is essential that the next generation of students are familiar with how to tidy, wrangle & interpret data. Find out how one of our fellows is doing just that with #ArcticData here: https://t.co/rczUsPMtdP https://t.co/c4GSw1K8bK
Thanks for the highlight - read on to learn more about the portals service! #opendata #arcticdata https://t.co/enikEHi0s6

#WednesdayWisdom: interested in what’s going on with the Navigating the New Arctic projects funded by @NSF? Lightning talk #videos, project update #reports, & summary notes from the April Investigators meeting are now up on the @ArcticResearch site! https://t.co/INWBaeSkSe https://t.co/3VkrSTUQXG
